            <div type="general">
               <head>General</head>
               <p xml:space="preserve">Testour is a small town located in North West Tunisia on the hills of Medjerda Valley. The population of Testour is famous for its Andalusian descent. The modern town occupies the site of the Roman settlement Tichilla which was granted to Andalusian refugees in 1609. </p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">As for the town’s tourist attractions, the main one is the Great Mosque built in Andalusian style in the 17th century. Furthermore, Testour hosts a yearly international festival of Malouf (traditional Andalusian music).</p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">The Andalusian roots of the inhabitants are also reflected in the lexis of the dialect of Testour, namely in some Andalusian Spanish loanwords. </p>
            </div>
            <div type="researchHistory">
               <head>Research history</head>
               <p xml:space="preserve">To the best of our knowledge hitherto no research has been done on the dialect of Testour, however this dialect is taken into consideration and examined within the TUNOCENT project.</p>
